Sentencas: Mass, heat and momentum transport processes are strongly coupled by internal chemical reforming reactions in planar design solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anodes.
Titulo: Analysis of parameter effects on chemical reaction coupled transport phenomena in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: In this paper, a three-dimensional computational fluid dynamics approach is applied to simulate and analyze reforming reactions of methane and various transport processes in a duct relevant for SOFC anodes.
Titulo: Analysis of parameter effects on chemical reaction coupled transport phenomena in SOFC anodes

Sentencas: The results show that the anode duct design and operating parameters, grouped as three characteristic ratios, are significant for the chemical reactions and further for multi-species distribution, fuel gas transport and heat transfer in the sub-domains of the anode.
Titulo: Analysis of parameter effects on chemical reaction coupled transport phenomena in SOFC anodes
